      "writtenOn": "2019-11-15T20:50:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Apparently nothing bad, since this hasn\u0027t been a problem before and seems to not be cause the problem in your case.\n\nIn most C implementations NULL is literally defined to 0:\n\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/aosp/toolchain/gcc/gcc-4.9/gcc/system.h;l\u003d44?q\u003d%22%23define%20NULL%22\u0026ss\u003dpiper%2FGoogle%2Fchromeos_public\n\nSo I don\u0027t think this change is buying us much, and it adds complexity to the clone()-ing code.",
